  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [x] Foundry\r\n- [ ] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (da73576 2022-06-04T00:13:25.46512185Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge install\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nSee transcript, it tries to install packages in the `lib` directory that does not exist under the current working directory.\r\n```\r\n%> forge install\r\nError: \r\n   0: error: pathspec '/home/magicking/source/gocode/src/github.com/Atlendis/schre/lib' did not match any file(s) known to git\r\n\r\nLocation:\r\n   cli/src/cmd/forge/install.rs:104\r\n```\r\nWith configuration being\r\n```\r\n%> cat foundry.toml\r\n[default]\r\nsrc = 'contracts/solidity/src'\r\nout = 'out'\r\nlibs = ['contracts/solidity/src/lib']\r\n```\r\nWith libs being `['lib']` by default, it seems that it should use the first item in `libs` rather than expecting the default directory being `lib`, see https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/da735765e7b5ebe524eece8315b4834edf48e994/cli/src/cmd/forge/install.rs#L93\r\n\r\nIt would ease integration with other tooling, that use or do not use a `lib` directory.",
